The REPL throws an NPE exception the second time you try to call a method that involves a type alias that's defined in a package object.

Repro steps:
(1) Unzip attachment -- contains the two source files, package.scala (where the type alias is defined) and Foo.scala (which defines the function using the type alias).
(2) Open a REPL
(3) Type: import com.mycompany.myproject.common.Foo
(4) Type: Foo.fromHex("abcd") -> 3 (success)
(5) Type (again): Foo.fromHex("abcd") -> NPEs

